emy Awards for Facebook marketing.</p><p>As a member of the Facebook Creative Council, I’m honored to be a member of this year’s jury.</p><p>We will be looking to hear how you used Facebook to connect with people, drive business growth and build personalized experiences. Here are a few criteria:</p><ul><li>Is the campaign inherently social? Are social interactions at the heart of the idea?</li><li>Are you maximizing the creative capabilities of Facebook? Are you making the Facebook experience better for users through your content?</li><li>Is it scalable? Is your idea easy to share and interact with, and does it have the potential and means to spread?</li><li>Does it drive business results? Are you strengthening the relationship you have with customers and increasing sales or conversions across Facebook?</li></ul><p>Are you excited yet? Do you want to join the ranks of some of last year’s winning campaigns, among them <a href=\"http://www.facebook-studio.com/awards/winners#/gallery/submission/small-business-saturday-2011\" target=\"_blank\">American Express’ Small Business Saturday 2011</a>, <a href=\"http://www.facebook-studio.com/awards/winners#/gallery/submission/serenading-unicorn-2011\">Wrigley’s Serenading Unicorn 2011</a> and <a href=\"http://www.facebook-studio.com/awards/winners#/gallery/submission/progress-thru-processors\">Intel’s Progress Thru Processors</a>?</p><p>Here’s how to enter: <a href=\"http://www.facebook-studio.com/awards/index\" target=\"_blank\">Head over to Facebook Studio</a> and click, “Submit Work” at the top of the page.</p><p>Enter soon: The deadline is December 31, 2012. I can’t wait to check out all of the great work!</p>
